bio: I am a fullstack developer and a graduate from the University of California, Irvine where I received a B.A. in Public Health Policy. During my studies, I learned about the world of telemedicine and how software development can be used to increase accessibility and provide better health outcomes.

I became seriously interested in pursuing a career in software development after trying out some free, introductory resources about coding. I then decided to invest in myself and enroll in LearningFuze, an immersive web development bootcamp.
I now have experience creating web applications using JavaScript, React.js, Node.js, PostgreSQL, and Express. I am always looking forward to expanding my skillset and learning more!
